Business Brief -- Pfizer Inc.:
   Koshin Medical, Wholesaler
   Of Equipment, Is Bought
The spokeswoman couldn't confirm a report in Friday
morning's Nihon Keizai Shimbun, a Japanese business, economic
and financial daily, that the purchase cost 300 million yen
($2.3 million) and that Sumitomo Bank Ltd. will be the
intermediary in the deal. Koshin Medical is capitalized at 30
million yen and had sales of roughly 4.5 billion yen in the
fiscal year ended in February 1991, the report said.